snippet.textDisplay: One thing I noticed is that the airfield being used is NAS (Naval Air Station) North Island, not MCAS (Marine Corps Air Base) Miramar (formerly NAS Miramar, the original home of TOPGUN, and the airfield in the original movie). This is interesting. In 1996, TOPGUN was transferred to NAS Fallon in Nevada, and NAS Miramar was then given to the Marine Corps and renamed MCAS Miramar, as it is today. Since the movie follows Navy pilots, it makes sense that they are using a Navy airfield rather than one belonging to the Marine Corps. Purposeful or not, interesting detail Paramount. As someone who grew up hearing those F-14s at Miramar a mile away everyday, I like it.
snippet.textOriginal: One thing I noticed is that the airfield being used is NAS (Naval Air Station) North Island, not MCAS (Marine Corps Air Base) Miramar (formerly NAS Miramar, the original home of TOPGUN, and the airfield in the original movie). Since the movie follows Navy pilots, it makes sense that they are using a Navy airfield rather than one belonging to the Marine Corps. Purposeful or not, interesting detail Paramount.
